        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-01-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-01-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="58" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d58">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/1–1549: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, [<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" when="1949-01-15">undated</date>].<lb/>[Received
                        January 15, 1949—3:33 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>184. Chauvel tells me he has instructed French Ambassador in Nanking to give
                    orally negative reply to Chinese.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
